        <a name="building">
        <h4>Getting and Building from source code</h4></a>
        
        <p>
            To use Wonderland Modules with Wonderland, you need to check out the 
            <code>wonderland-modules</code> project and re-build <code>lg3d-wonderland</code>.
        </p>
        <p>
            Follow these steps to checkout and build the <code>wonderland-modules</code> project:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Change directory to the parent directory of <code>lg3d-wonderland</code>
            </li>
            <li>
                Check out source code with a Subversion client using the following command:
                Note: replace the last <code>username</code> with your own username.
                <p>
                    <code>svn checkout https://wonderland-modules.dev.java.net/svn/wonderland-modules/trunk wonderland-modules --username username</code>
                </p>
                <p>
                    If you are new to Subversion, you may want to visit the <a href="http://subversion.tigris.org/">Subversion Project website</a>
                    and read <a href="http://svnbook.red-bean.com/">Version Control with Subversion</a>.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                Change directory to <code>lg3d-wonderland</code>:
                <p>
                    <code>cd lg3d-wonderland</code>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                Build the <code>lg3d-wonderland</code> project:
                <p>
                    <code>ant</code>
                </p>
                <p>
                    You can also build the project in netbeans.
                </p>
                <p>
                <b>Note:</b> Wonderland modules can only be built from the <code>lg3d-wonderland</code>
                project.
            </li>
        </ul>
        
        <a name="loading">
        <h4>Loading a module into Wonderland</h4></a>
        
        <p>
            Modules are loaded using WFS. Each module contains a WFS property file, 
            which provides Wonderland with the information it need to load the module
            and initialize it.
        </p>
        <p>
            For example, the PDF Viewer's WFS property file is located here:
        </p>
        <p>
            <code>wonderland-modules/src/modules/apps/2d/pdfviewer/PDFViewer-wlc.xml</code>
        </p>
        <p>
            To load the PDF Viewer module into the default Wonderland world, follow these steps:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Change directory to the building in the default world:
                <p>
                    <code>cd lg3d-wonderland/src/worlds/default-wfs/building-wld</code>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>Now change directory to the Demo Floor region:
            <p>
                <code>cd DemoFloor-wld</code>
            </p>
            <li>Now copy the PDF Viewer's WFS property file into this directory:
                <p>
                    <code>cp ../../../../../../wonderland-modules/src/modules/apps/2d/pdfviewer/PDFViewer-wlc.xml .</code>
                </p>
                <p>
                    The property file specifies the following properties:
                    <ul>
                        <li>The URL of the PDF document to open<br/>
                            Note that this URL must be accessible by all Wonderland clients
                        </li>
                        <li>The preferred width and height of the PDF Viewer application window<br>
                            (defaults to 791x1024 (matches the aspect ratio of an 8.5"x11" page))
                        </li>
                        <li>The page to open<br/>
                            (defaults to the first page)
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>Restart the Wonderland server on the system where you installed the WFS property file:
                <p>
                    <code>ant run-sgs</code>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>Now start the Wonderland client:
                <p>
                    <code>ant run</code>
                </p>
                <p>
                    You should see a message indicating that the PDF Viewer is loading a document.
                    When the client has finished initializing, you should see the document in front
                    of you at the default entry point into the world.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                
                <p>
                    To interact with the application, first take control with a <code>shift+left mouse click</code>
                    on the application.
                </p>
                <p>
                    To change pages, use <code>PageUp</code> and <code>PageDown</code>. You can also use the
                    mouse wheel.
                </p>
                <p>
                    If the page is taller then the window, you can drag it up and down with the left mouse
                    button.
                </p>
                <p>
                To open a new document, press <code>ctrl+o</code> and enter the URL of the document 
                in the dialog.
                <p>
            </li>
        </ul>
